# LifeTracker Pro API Examples
# This file can be used with the REST Client extension in VS Code
# or with tools like Insomnia, Postman, or curl

### Health check
GET http://localhost:3001/api/health

### Get all goals
GET http://localhost:3001/api/goals
Content-Type: application/json

### Get goal by ID
GET http://localhost:3001/api/goals/goal-1
Content-Type: application/json

### Create new goal - CORRECT FORMAT
POST http://localhost:3001/api/goals
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Run 5K",
  "targetDate": "2023-12-31T00:00:00.000Z",
  "notes": "Train 3 times per week",
  "achieved": false,
  "progress": 20
}

### INCORRECT FORMAT - Don't do this (escape issues)
# This is incorrect because the JSON is escaped - the API expects proper JSON objects
POST http://localhost:3001/api/goals
Content-Type: application/json

'{\'title\':\'Run 5K\',\'targetDate\':\'2023-12-31\'}'

### INCORRECT FORMAT - Don't do this (string format)
# This is incorrect because it's already a string, not a JSON object
POST http://localhost:3001/api/goals
Content-Type: application/json

"{\"title\":\"Run 5K\",\"targetDate\":\"2023-12-31\"}"

### Update goal
PUT http://localhost:3001/api/goals/goal-1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Run 10K",
  "progress": 45
}

### Delete goal
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/goals/goal-1
Content-Type: application/json 